ed variability of many ultraviolet\nlines is most likely of atmospheric origin and reflects the inhomogeneous\nelemental surface distribution. The variability of the Civ resonance lines is\nstronger and it probably results from the dependence of the wind mass-loss rate\non the chemical composition and magnetic field orientation. We have not been\nable to detect a clear signature of the matter trapped in the circumstellar\nclouds.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 11 Jun 2013 09:12:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-16"}
