ss, with one of them being spheroid-like, and\nthe other providing the first confirmation of a passive lenticular galaxy at a\nspectroscopically derived redshift z~2.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 11 Jun 2013 12:02:27 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 7 Sep 2013 17:33:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-16"}
